>   Why not simply modify the floppy driver to keep the floppy motor
> on while the disk is mounted? People are `trained' not to eject 
> the disk while the light is on....
   Because there are machines with floppy disks inserted for weeks
(once I had a router using floppy as root) and it isn't wise to keep
the motor on if you don't touch the diskette at all.
